data.name: RoundRobinDescription
data.value: The Round Robin algorithm is a system where each team meets all the other teams. If the championship includes an odd number of teams, one team remains without a match each day.

data.name: SwissSystemDescription
data.value: The Swiss system algorithm is a system where all teams play the same number of matches against random opponents. This system is particularly useful for tournaments where the number of participants is too large to allow a full round-robin but where fair ranking is still necessary after a limited number of matches. It can only be used for an even number of teams.
